CAPTURE INTEGRALS OF THE LANTHANIDE NUCLEI CE-140,
JEEP 2 HEAVY WATER REACTOR, SAMPLES WERE
IRRADIATED BOTH IN A THERMAL COLUMN(2 HOURS TO 3 DAYS)
WITH A FLUX DENSITY OF ABOUT 1.0E+10 N/CM-SQ/SEC AND
IN THE CENTRE OF THE CORE WITH A FLUX DENSITY OF
ACTIVATION MEASUREMENTS ON THE GOLD FLUX MONITOR.

.THE RESULT GIVEN IS THE AVARAGE OVER ALL THE
